Viola rotundifolia is a species of flowering plant in the family Violaceae. 
It is also known as round-leaved yellow violet or smooth yellow violet. 
The plant has rounded leaves that are smooth and shiny, with jagged edges. 
It produces bright yellow flowers with five petals that bloom in early spring. 
The plant typically grows in wooded areas, particularly in moist soil and partial shade. 
It is native to eastern North America, and can be found from Canada to the southeastern United States. 
Viola rotundifolia is sometimes used in traditional medicine and herbal remedies for respiratory and digestive ailments.
